claim.claim-text:
21. A test tool for cell site testing, comprising:
a base module containing electrical components to provide common base testing of a device-under-test (DUT), wherein the base module includes a top surface and a bottom surface having recesses;
at least one expansion module removably connected to the bottom surface of the base module, wherein the at least one expansion module includes cleats that fit into the recesses in the bottom surface of the base module;
at least one solution module removably connected to the top surface of the base module, wherein the at least one solution module is to receive power and communication from the base module; and
an input/output (I/O) module removably connected to a top of the at least one solution module to receive the power and communication from the base module through the at least one solution module and to display information,
wherein the base module, the at least one expansion module, the at least one solution module, and the I/O module are integrated into a single unified device.

30. A test tool for cell site testing, comprising:
a base module containing electrical components to provide common base testing of a device-under-test (DUT), the common base testing including power meter testing, talkset-datalink testing, and Visual Fault Locator testing, wherein the base module includes a top surface having a first top interface and a bottom surface having a first bottom interface and a first recess;
a first expansion module removably connected to the bottom surface of the base module, wherein the first expansion module includes a first expansion interface connected to the first bottom interface of the base module and a first cleat that fits into the first recess in the bottom surface of the base module, and wherein the first expansion module communicates electrical communication and power with the base module via the first expansion interface;
a first solution module removably connected to the top surface of the base module, wherein the first solution module includes a first solution interface connected to the first top interface of the base module to receive power and communication from the base module; and
an input/output (I/O) module removably connected to a top of the first solution module, the I/O module comprising a display to provide information, wherein the first solution module provides the power and communication received from the base module to the I/O module,
wherein the base module, the first expansion module, the first solution module, and the I/O module are integrated into a single unified device.
